sp_scores.title: Exploit Gwitch's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Galeedo's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Daguza's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Daguza, Gwitch, and Galeedo don't use anything besides physical attacks, so use Protect to take the wind out of their sails! Gwitch uses Cure, so attack him with his weakness, fire, to bring him down first, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Daguza, Gwitch, & Galeedo

dungeons.epilogue: Vaan quickly found himself outnumbered, but with Balthier's help, managed to defeat Daguza. Together, they looked for a way out, wandering into an oubliette where they found Basch suspended in a cage. With Imperials approaching, they jumped onto the cage and lowered it, escaping into the dungeon depths.
dungeons.name: Nalbina Dungeons
dungeons.prologue: Vaan awakens in the Nalbina Dungeons, where he intervenes to stop the jailor Daguza and his lackeys from abusing a bangaa prisoner.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Mimic Queen's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: Mimic Queen wields powerful lightning and earth group attacks, kupo! Use abilities like Magic Break and Shell to shore up your defenses, then strike back with her weakness, ice!
tip_battle.title: Mimic Queen

dungeons.epilogue: Learning that Vaan was Reks's brother, Basch began to tell him the truth of what happened two years earlier. The assassination had been an Imperial plot, and it was Basch's twin brother Judge Gabranth who killed Reks, not Basch. The party made their way through the passage, defeating a Mimic Queen before finally emerging in the desert.
dungeons.name: Barheim Passage
dungeons.prologue: The cage lands in the Barheim Passage, a monster-infested network of tunnels. Basch joins the party as they make their way back to the surface.

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Air Cutter Remora without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Air Cutter Remora uses a powerful group attack, kupo! Abilities like Power Break and Protect can help cut down the damage!
tip_battle.title: Air Cutter Remora

dungeons.epilogue: Basch, Vossler, and Reks were among the knights making their way through Nalbina Fortress when they were confronted by Imperial soldiers. Sending the others on ahead, Reks was dealing with their pursuers when he entered the throne room to find King Raminas among the many dead lying there. Basch appeared before Reks and ran him through with his sword, leaving the young knight to fall despairing into darkness.
dungeons.name: Nalbina Fortress
dungeons.prologue: Vaan's brother Reks is part of the team trying to stop the assassination set to take place at the signing of Dalmasca's surrender to Archadia.

tip_battle.message: Ba'Gamnan and his crew use every attack but the kitchen sink, kupo! But they're all vulnerable to water! Focus your attacks and bring them down one by one!
tip_battle.title: Ba'Gamnan, Bwagi, Rinok, & Gijuk

dungeons.epilogue: While en route to the Lhusu Mines beneath the Skycity of Bhujerba, the party was joined by a well-spoken youth calling himself Lamont. Reaching the mines, Lamont produced a shard of manufacted nethicite, developed by the Empire, and began comparing it with the natural magicite in the mines. Balthier was wondering why the boy would have such a thing when Ba'Gamnan attacked the party, and Lamont disappeared in the struggle.
dungeons.name: Lhusu Mines
dungeons.prologue: The party heads for the Lhusu Mines to rescue Penelo, who has been taken prisoner by Ba'Gamnan and his cronies.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Flans' weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Physical attacks don't do much to Flans, but magic sure does, kupo! Especially fire magic! Since you face 4 of them at once, and they heal each other, Ifrit or other fire damage that hits them all at once is your best bet!
tip_battle.title: Flan

sp_scores.title: Exploit Firemane's weakness to water attacks.

tip_battle.message: Firemane uses a group fire attack that Poisons, kupo! Take it out fast with water, its greatest weakness!
tip_battle.title: Firemane

dungeons.epilogue: The two whom Vaan met in the palace treasury were none other than the sky pirate Balthier and his partner, Fran. Vaan accompanied them through the waterway where they encountered Amalia, a member of the resistance, fighting against Imperial troops. Amalia joined the party, and helped them fight their way out past Firemane, only to be surrounded by Imperials and taken captive.
dungeons.name: Garamsythe Waterway
dungeons.prologue: Vaan has snuck into Rabanastre Palace, where he meets a dashing man and his viera partner. The two help Vaan escape on their airbike before careening down to a crash landing in the Garamsythe Waterway.
